理查德·拉塞尔
Richard Russell.

98
00:05:21,770 --> 00:05:22,830
{\an8}长期反对民权运动

99
00:05:22,830 --> 00:05:25,230
1963年  《民权法案》
Civil Rights Act. 1963.

100
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:27,460
不是所有人都能留下美名
Not everyone can be on the right side of history.

101
00:05:27,460 --> 00:05:29,110
连林登也曾站错队
No, not even Lyndon for a time,

102
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:31,740
但没有拉塞尔  林登也当不上多数党领袖
but he would have never become majority leader without him.

103
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:34,430
但是没有约翰逊参议院大楼
Well, there's no Johnson Senate building.

104
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:34,430
{\an8}有拉塞尔参议院大楼

105
00:05:34,430 --> 00:05:37,580
是啊  只能委屈他拿一栋总统图书馆凑合了
No. He had to settle for a presidential library.

106
00:05:38,060 --> 00:05:40,760
我们都好久没机会聊聊了
So it's been some time since you and I have had a chance to catch up.

107
00:05:40,760 --> 00:05:42,500
你的工作做得很出色  杰姬
You've been an outstanding deputy, Jackie.

108
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:45,340
比你那些老练的同事还高效
Far more effective than your more seasoned colleagues.

109
00:05:45,340 --> 00:05:48,220
你能建立同盟  必要时还有股狠劲
You're a coalition builder, a fighter when you have to be.

110
00:05:48,930 --> 00:05:51,340
告诉我  你怎么看自己的前途
Tell me, where do you see yourself headed?

111
00:05:52,830 --> 00:05:55,900
我想做众议院军事委员会主席
I'd like to aim for the chair of Armed Services.

112
00:05:55,900 --> 00:05:57,360
或者众议院国土安全委员会主席
Or Homeland Security.

113
00:05:57,510 --> 00:05:59,930
你考虑过进入领导层吗
Have you ever considered serving in the leadership?

114
00:06:00,940 --> 00:06:03,870
我想那至少也得等八...十年了
I figure that might be possible eight, ten years from now.

115
00:06:03,870 --> 00:06:07,440
如果我说你这一届就能进入领导层呢
Well, what if I suggested that you could serve in leadership this term.

116
00:06:08,180 --> 00:06:11,060
接替我  做党鞭
To replace me. As whip.

117
00:06:12,850 --> 00:06:14,370
你要接任副总统了
You're being tapped for VP.

118
00:06:14,370 --> 00:06:16,050
就算是这样吧
Let's assume that's true.

119
00:06:16,630 --> 00:06:20,870
-这也说得通  但我做党鞭  -是的
- Well, that makes sense. But me as whip? - Yes.

120
00:06:20,870 --> 00:06:22,040
我只是个第三任女议员
A third-term congresswoman?

121
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:26,900
你的能力有目共睹  而且还参过战
A universally admired incumbent who also happens to be a war veteran.

122
00:06:26,900 --> 00:06:29,550
按顺序也该是韦伯  或巴克沃特
Webb is next in line. Or Buchwalter.

123
00:06:32,060 --> 00:06:34,870
所以  你想想这意味着什么
So just consider that for a moment.

124
00:06:38,570 --> 00:06:40,530
他们会牵制彼此的选票
They'll draw votes from one another.

125
00:06:41,770 --> 00:06:43,470
我可没说你会赢得很轻松
Oh, I'm not saying you wouldn't have to fight for it,

126
00:06:43,470 --> 00:06:45,390
但我愿意帮你
but I'd be willing to give you the ammunition.

127
00:06:47,830 --> 00:06:48,940
过来
Come over here.

128
00:06:55,510 --> 00:06:56,560
这是什么
What is this?

129
00:06:57,140 --> 00:07:00,100
我关于韦伯和巴克沃特的文件
My files on Webb and Buchwalter.

130
00:07:00,100 --> 00:07:01,300
你自己看看吧
Why don't you take a look?

131
00:07:01,750 --> 00:07:03,390
我们过几天再谈
We'll speak in a few days.

132
00:07:04,060 --> 00:07:06,030
还有一个关于你的文件夹
Oh, and, uh, there's one on you.

133
00:07:06,030 --> 00:07:08,400
或许你会想先读那个
You might want to begin by reading that one first.

134
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:31,930
简宁怎么说
What'd Janine say?

135
00:07:31,940 --> 00:07:33,650
脱衣舞俱乐部还没开
Strip club's not open yet.

136
00:07:34,350 --> 00:07:35,840
你去查科佩尼科的事吗
You'll look into Kapeniak?

137
00:07:35,840 --> 00:07:37,660
如果他出现  我就能找到他
If he's on the grid, I'll find him.

138
00:07:39,850 --> 00:07:42,310
-送我去地铁中心站  -不去办公室吗
- Drop me at metro center. - Not the office?

139
00:07:43,220 --> 00:07:44,670
我要去找瑞秋
I'm gonna talk to Rachel.

140
00:07:45,650 --> 00:07:47,890
她会像昨晚那样否认一切的
She'll deny everything, like she did last night.

141
00:07:47,890 --> 00:07:50,570
她不能否认上了斯坦普的车  你看到她了
She can't deny getting into Stamper's car. You saw her.

142
00:07:52,350 --> 00:07:54,680
或许你可以拿篇报道她爸爸的稿子给她看
Maybe you send a version of the story, about her dad?

143
00:07:55,260 --> 00:07:56,710
没人会发表的
No one would print it.

144
00:07:57,730 --> 00:07:58,990
可瑞秋不知道啊
Rachel doesn't know that.

145
00:07:59,380 --> 00:08:01,390
她说"随你便  贱人"
She said, "Go to town, bitch."

146
00:08:01,390 --> 00:08:03,360
不会管用的  我得当面跟她谈
It won't work. I have to get in her face.

147
00:08:09,350 --> 00:08:10,610
恭喜
Congratulations.

148
00:08:12,570 --> 00:08:14,250
-我们都替你高兴  -谢谢
- We're thrilled for you. - Thank you.

149
00:08:14,250 --> 00:08:16,290
我想亲自跟鲍勃和泰瑞说
I wanted to fill in Bob and Terry personally.

150
00:08:16,490 --> 00:08:19,280
我们快开始吧  我什么时候出发去匹兹堡
Now let's get to it. I have to leave for Pittsburgh in what?

151
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:20,200
20分钟后
20 minutes.

152
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:22,210
帮吉姆冲刺  就要到终点了
Home stretch with Jim. Whistle-stop tour.

153
00:08:22,210 --> 00:08:23,290
现在形势很好
Looking good out there.

154
00:08:23,290 --> 00:08:25,170
的确  但我们还是不想冒险
Very good. But we don't want to take any chances.

155
00:08:25,170 --> 00:08:27,080
接替你的党鞭人选  弗兰克
Now, your replacement as whip, Frank.

156
00:08:27,090 --> 00:08:28,800
鲍勃已经提出了一些想法
Bob has already shared some thoughts.

157
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:29,840
我喜欢霍华德·韦伯
I like Howard Webb.

158
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:32,800
韦伯不错  你考虑过韦斯·巴克沃特吗
Webb is a solid choice. Have you thought about Wes Buchwalter?

159
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:34,210
巴克沃特太冲动
Buchwalter's a hot-head.

160
00:08:34,210 --> 00:08:36,280
那么韦伯你觉得可以吗  弗兰克
Well, could you live with Webb, Frank?

161
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:38,880
韦伯懂战术  但做事虎头蛇尾
Webb is a good tactician, but he lacks follow-through.

162
00:08:38,880 --> 00:08:41,280
巴克沃特是个粗人
The problem with Buchwalter is he's too abrasive.

163
00:08:41,280 --> 00:08:43,100
毫无魅力  树敌太多
No charm. Lots of enemies.

164
00:08:43,100 --> 00:08:44,070
还有别的选择吗
Is there a third option?

165
00:08:44,070 --> 00:08:46,370
他们是党团资历最深的两位  轮到他们了
They're the two most senior members in the caucus. It's their turn.

166
00:08:46,370 --> 00:08:48,830
总统先生  可不可以让党内成员一起挑选
Mr. President, what if we let the caucus pick?

167
00:08:48,830 --> 00:08:51,350
大家公平竞争  他们两人都很有资质
Let it be a wide-open race. Both men are qualified.

168
00:08:51,350 --> 00:08:53,160
领导层在这事上要意见一致
The leadership should be united in this.

169
00:08:53,160 --> 00:08:54,980
我们不能各自支持不同的候选人  弗兰克
We don't want to be backing different candidates, Frank.

170
00:08:54,980 --> 00:08:57,260
那我们就干脆别插手  谁都别支持谁
So we stay out of it and neither of us backs anyone.

171
00:08:57,260 --> 00:08:57,940
这挺好
I like it.

172
00:08:57,940 --> 00:09:00,680
党团会尊重凭实力竞争上来的人
Caucus will respect someone who did it the old-fashioned way.

173
00:09:01,110 --> 00:09:03,350
几位  这事你们做主
Well, gentlemen, it's your call to make.

174
00:09:03,350 --> 00:09:05,640
你们自己讨论决定  然后告诉我
Figure it out amongst yourselves. Let me know what you decide.

175
00:09:05,640 --> 00:09:06,870
谢谢  总统先生
Thank you, Mr. President.

176
00:09:08,610 --> 00:09:10,370
帮我接刘易斯部长
Put me through to Secretary Lewis.

177
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:13,570
弗兰克  我不想为这事跟你争
Frank, I don't want to go to battle with you on this.

178
00:09:13,570 --> 00:09:14,630
我们犯过这种错
We've been down that road.

179
00:09:14,630 --> 00:09:15,890
说得是啊
I couldn't agree more.

180
00:09:15,890 --> 00:09:17,240
公平竞争让我紧张
An open race makes me nervous.

181
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:19,300
我只是提议一下
Well, look, it was just a suggestion.

182
00:09:20,070 --> 00:09:22,290
